sendMessage.description:
Use this key to send a message to the chat.

- Workflow has to be started by a chat node.
- Put execution to wait after sending.

See example in
packages/@n8n/nodes-langchain/nodes/trigger/ChatTrigger/Chat.node.ts

NodeApiError.description:
Class for instantiating an error in an API response, e.g. a 404 Not Found response,
with an HTTP error code, an error message and a description.

setDefaultStatusCodeMessage.description: Set the error's message based on the HTTP status code.

NodeOperationError.description: Class for instantiating an operational error, e.g. an invalid credentials error.

executionContext.description:
Execution context carries per-execution metadata throughout workflow lifecycle
Established at execution start and propagated to sub-workflows/error workflows

size.description: The total number of parameter entries.

closed.description: Is true after 'close' has been emitted.

errored.description: Returns error if the stream has been destroyed with an error.

readable.description:
Is `true` if it is safe to call `readable.read()`, which means
the stream has not been destroyed or emitted `'error'` or `'end'`.

readableAborted.description: Returns whether the stream was destroyed or errored before emitting `'end'`.

readableEncoding.description: Getter for the property `encoding` of a given `Readable` stream. The `encoding`property can be set using the `readable.setEncoding()` method.

readableFlowing.description:
This property reflects the current state of a `Readable` stream as described
in the `Three states` section.

readableHighWaterMark.description: Returns the value of `highWaterMark` passed when creating this `Readable`.

readableLength.description:
This property contains the number of bytes (or objects) in the queue
ready to be read. The value provides introspection data regarding
the status of the `highWaterMark`.

readableObjectMode.description: Getter for the property `objectMode` of a given `Readable` stream.
